Author: relativelypositive#0493
Content:
Okay I'm sure this has already been said but lets be clear here:

The particular stand he is using is a cheap geode with a pole in the middle, and the fish is simply balanced on top, since it needs to not be attached in any way to it at risk of lowering its value.

That being said as an artist I'm pretty familiar with this stand: there is NO WAY to control what angle the fish is point other than a general left and right, and even at that its not easy.

This laid out, I am pointing out a few things.
1. Before and after each cut his head is looking up as though he had been checking on the fish to make sure its okay.

2. After the first cut when the fish seemed to be spinning around a little towards the other direction, the cut is oddly timed between a word, and the fish is very clearly repositioned to face the same direction it was before, but he's holding it differently for more stability. This is a fix, he wants the fish to stay in that direction.

3. After the phrase "beyond a fact", the direction chances to the opposite facing way, and stays that way the rest of the song.

That is what we know about the fish direction. This is the only thing he controls about the fish position is the over all left-right direction it is facing.

Author: relativelypositive#0493
Content: Feel free to use this for wherever you're at or share it, I'm just really tired of seeing the angle theory when there's just no way with the construction of that thing. üòÇüòÇüòÇ

Author: kindnessiskey#6625

Author: squarepx#1263
Content: old compasses were actually like a magnetic fish model, floating in a bowl. There's a few google images of it or just look up history of compass

Author: kindnessiskey#6625
Content: How interesting

Author: relativelypositive#0493
Content: Yes you can make a compass with a magnetized paperclip on a leaf in some water. And that fish is balanced as though it is sitting in a bowl of water spinning. But it is not magnetized (pretty sure the metal used is in the fish non magnetic but did not look that up yet), and there is no way he would attach magnets to something that valuable, and he is not controlling the specific angle it is facing, only the general left or right direction.

Author: relativelypositive#0493
Content: So no "reading into the angle" theories, only that its facing one direction and at a specific point faces the other direction--read into that fact as much as you want.

Content:
Decided to delete and make a actual serious post based on what everyone is saying and my logic of the song:

**In the name of Max Fosh, dish out the fish. ** - Draw the fish out of Max Fosh(the name).
**Neighbour on the bus or a dear old queen **- There is nothing here. These are possible ways(putting together and spoonerism) you can manipulate the fish out of the name and Max is telling us the different ways.....why they were so easy to solve.
**With the possibility the world is packed** - As already said, the World = Earth(maybe).......Earth being packed could refer to when dirt is packed. As in when you press down on the soil after you bury something.
**But the keeper of the secret is not close to Max** - I think this will be solved with Classic Crossword Cryptography. I believe solving "In the name of Max Fosh" will result in a dual meaning that is both the new answer and a actual type of synonym "Keeper"..  So, The keeper of the secret is the Straight Part. And In the name of Max Fosh is the Cryptic. ORRRR The Keeper of the Secret is the Straight and, simply, "is not close to Max" the cryptic.

I think this right here is a condensed version of what I believe alot of people are coming to the conclusion right now so I think this is one of the worthwhile things for me to say right now.

reasons:

b) there are a few interesting decisions i talked about yesterday in the chinese text, for example in chinese it does say goldfish instead of trout. I guess it says trout just to rhyme in english. there are more, I'm sure.

Content:
I don't think we can be confident that sooonerisms are involved, but it's a possibility.  

From the original song, it's possible to get to the idea through 'Dear old queen' and 'Song silly' (though song silly doesn't necessarily imply spoonerism)

The point of the hint is to confirm what kind of strategy we should be using, "melpful histake" isn't really a spoonerism, but it does seem to hint at it
